default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAccording to the UN Convention on the Rights of 
defaultthe Child
default, 
defaultchildren 
defaultwith disabilities have the right to 
defaulta 
defaultfull
default and decent life
default, 
defaultto 
defaultequally and meaningfully participate in and benefit from humanitarian
default assistance and development processes in their communities
default. However
default,
default the rights of 
defaultthese 
defaultchildren 
defaultmay be violated by attitudinal, institutional or environmental barriers that exist in any given society. Every community or society has barriers that prevent
default some of its members (especially those with physical, sensory or intellectual impairments) from participating in activities that other members of society enjoy. 
