default18.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn 2011, World Vision UK was awarded a second PPA grant, with a new focus on child protection. 
defaultO
defaultur goal to ensure ‘children and communities, especially the most vulnerable and those in the poorest and/or most fragile contexts, are cared and protected’ ha
defaults mainstreamed disability into its programmes. Baseline and monitoring data for this PPA outcome is disaggregated by disability, to ensure levels of inclusion are measured
default and reflected upon
default. Mainstreaming disability into child protection programming has a
defaultlso contributed to a change in social norms around 
defaultthe inclusion of certain groups
default in development processes and 
defaulthas 
defaultled to decreased levels of prejudice in the community. What is currently 
defaultmissing
default from DFID reporting is the lack of clear disaggregated data
default on the numbers of PWDs and specifically CWDs in targeted areas, being reached and impacted. We call on DFID to demand clear, disaggregated data from projects they fund. 
defaultIf
default this 
defaultproves logistically challenging, DFID should provide enough funds to ensure th
defaultis standard of data is still provided
default.
