defaultTargeting disability in fragile states default&#xa0;
default20.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWorld Vision UK focuses on reaching the most vulnerable people 
defaultliving 
defaultin the 
defaultworld’s toughest 
defaultplaces. We deliberately choose to work in fragi
defaultle contexts where communities are often recovering from conflict and in areas where the national government is not fulfilling its responsibilities
default to its citizens.
default Research suggests that children with disabilities experience violence at a greater rate of 
default1.7 annually than able-bodied youths
default. 
defaultUNICEF 
defaultestimate
defaults
default 
defaultfor every 1 child that is killed as a consequence of armed violence, 3 children are left with permanent, life-long injuries or disabilities. Between
default 1990 and 2001, 6 million more had been left disabled
default. 
defaultIn natural disasters and conflicts, the needs of CWDs are often neglected and these individuals become ‘forgotten victims’
default of the emergency
default.
default In these areas, we are aware that impairments may not only
default affect an individual at birth but it may also be the consequence of living in these conditions
default and our programmes reflect this
default. 
